Press Releases.Title: 47 New Cases of Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 8 September 2020, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed an additional 47 cases of COVID-19 infection in Singapore. Based on our investigations so far, there are no cases in the community. 

2      There is 1 imported case, who had been placed on Stay-Home Notice upon arrival in Singapore. 

3      We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight.

 

MINISTRY OF HEALTH
8 SEPTEMBER 2020
